"{\"uid\": \"publicist24.com-mass-eviction-from-frances-largest-squat-sparks-outcry-ahead-of-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Situated in the southern suburb of Vitry-sur-Seine, the squat, housed in an abandoned bus company headquarters, had been a refuge for up to 450 individuals, many of whom were refugees, asylum seekers, or homeless  In the shadow of the eagerly anticipated Paris Olympics, the city finds itself embroiled in controversy as authorities evict hundreds from what was once the largest squat in France.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35, \"end\": 50, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vitry-sur-Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.167866048021681e-20, \"text\": \"Vitry-sur-Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vitry-sur-Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vitry-sur-Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 388, \"end\": 394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997761866004281, \"rank\": 0.00022366863473363607, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Situated in the southern suburb of Vitry-sur-Seine, the squat, housed in an abandoned bus company headquarters, had been a refuge for up to 450 individuals, many of whom were refugees, asylum seekers, orhomeless.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 432, \"end\": 447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vitry-sur-Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.167866048021681e-20, \"text\": \"Vitry-sur-Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vitry-sur-Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vitry-sur-Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The eviction, executed by police clad in riot gear, commenced at dawn, coinciding with France's celebration of 100 days until the commencement of the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997761866004281, \"rank\": 0.00022366863473363607, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The timing has sparked fresh accusations from charitable organizations that the government is orchestrating a campaign to clear the capital and its environs of marginalized communities before the global spotlight shines on Paris.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 1004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 998, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.0479142666317816e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the residents of the Vitry-sur-Seine squat gathered their belongings and departed, they were encouraged to board buses bound for other parts ofFrance.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, many expressed reluctance to leave the Paris region, where they had secured employment and established lives despite the challenges of finding proper housing.\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.0479142666317816e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among those affected were 50 women and 20 children, with at least 10 children enrolled in local schools.\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The squat's population had surged following the eviction of hundreds from another squat in \\u00cele-Saint-Denis, near theOlympic Village site, underscoring the interconnectedness of housing insecurity and large-scale events like the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1672, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paul Alauzy, a spokesperson for M\\u00e9decins du Monde and Revers de la M\\u00e9daille, decried what he termed \\\"social cleansing for the Olympic Games,\\\" highlighting a pattern of evictions targeting vulnerable communities over the past year.\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Alauzy, the population of the Vitry-sur-Seine squat had swelled due to the displacement caused by previous clearances, illustrating the collateral damage inflicted by efforts to beautify Paris for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 2129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2106, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.0479142666317816e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He revealed that the majority of the squat's residents possessed legal documentation, including refugee status or asylum seeker permits, and many held jobs in various sectors.\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, systemic barriers, such as discrimination from landlords, hindered their ability to secure permanent housing, exacerbating their precarious living situation.\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2474, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jhila Prentis, a volunteer at the squat, emphasized that the housing crisis predates the Olympics, with eviction rates escalating in recent months.\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She pointed out that while the building lacked planning permission, another evicted site in \\u00cele-Saint-Denis remains vacant, fueling suspicions that the clearances are aimed at creating a sanitized image of Paris for international visitors.\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2831, \"end\": 2836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.0479142666317816e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The eviction has reignited debates about the prioritization of urban development over the welfare of marginalized communities, particularly amidst the backdrop of a global sporting event.\", \"from\": 2866, \"to\": 3053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Critics argue that while the Olympics promise economic benefits and cultural exchange, they should not come at the expense of human rights and social justice.\", \"from\": 3055, \"to\": 3213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to inquiries, local authorities cited safety concerns and legal irregularities as justification for the eviction, asserting their commitment to upholding the law.\", \"from\": 3215, \"to\": 3389, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, calls for a more compassionate and sustainable approach to addressing homelessness and housing insecurity persist, with activists urging policymakers to prioritize long-term solutions over short-term aesthetic improvements.\", \"from\": 3391, \"to\": 3623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As Paris prepares to welcome athletes and spectators from around the world, the specter of displacement casts a shadow over the city's festivities, prompting reflection on the true legacy of mega-events in the urban landscape.\", \"from\": 3625, \"to\": 3851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3628, \"end\": 3633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.0479142666317816e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, 